From: Peios <kernel@peios.org>
Subject: FACS patch 5: skip credential swap in do_faccessat

On Peios, setuid does not exist. The credential swap in access()
evaluates the primary token instead of the effective token. Add
security_access_use_effective() hook — returns nonzero to skip
the swap. KACS always returns true.

--- a/fs/open.c
+++ b/fs/open.c
@@ -391,4 +391,7 @@
 	const struct cred *cred;

+	if (security_access_use_effective())
+		return false;
+
 	if (flags & AT_EACCESS)
 		return false;
